er]]\n| [[Aprilia]]\n| 17\n| Accident\n| 9\n|\n|-\n! Ret\n| 8\n| {{flagicon|JPN}} [[Masao Azuma]]\n| [[Honda]]\n| 14\n| Accident\n| 32\n|\n|-\n! Ret\n| 52\n| {{flagicon|DEU}} [[Jarno M\u00fcller]]\n| [[Honda]]\n| 14\n| Retirement\n| 34\n|\n|-\n! Ret\n| 91\n| {{flagicon|DEU}} [[Jascha B\u00fcch]]\n| [[Honda]]\n| 12\n| Accident\n| 30\n|\n|-\n! Ret\n| 33\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Stefano Bianco]]\n| [[Gilera]]\n| 11\n| Retirement\n| 33\n|\n|-\n! Ret\n| 1\n| {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Arnaud Vincent]]\n| [[KTM]]\n| 9\n| Accident\n| 24\n|\n|-\n! Ret\n| 53\n| {{flagicon|DEU}} [[Manuel Mickan]]\n| [[Honda]]\n| 7\n| Accident\n| 27\n|\n|-\n! Ret\n| 26\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Emilio Alzamora]]\n| [[Derbi]]\n| 7\n| Retirement\n| 28\n|\n|-\n! Ret\n| 63\n| {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Mike Di Meglio]]\n| [[Aprilia]]\n| 2\n| Accident\n| 31\n|\n|-\n! Ret\n| 25\n| {{flagicon|HUN}} [[Imre T\u00f3th]]\n| [[Honda]]\n| 2\n| Retirement\n| 26\n|\n|-\n! DNS\n| 11\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Max Sabbatani]]\n| [[Aprilia]]\n|\n| Did not start\n|\n|\n|-\n!colspan=8| Source: <ref>{{cite web|url=http://resources.motogp.com/files/results/2003/125cc/GER/RAC/classification.pdf|title=Cinzano Motorrad GP Deutschland&nbsp;\u2013 125cc&nbsp;\u2013 Race Classification|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]|date=27 July 2003|accessdate=2 May 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Championship standings after the race (motoGP)==\n\nBelow are the standings for the top five riders and constructors after round nine has concluded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.crash.net/motogp/news/72833/1/world-championship-standings|title=World Championship standings.|date=July 27, 2003|website=Crash}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://resources.motogp.com/files/results/2003/500cc/GER/world+standing.pdf?v1_96143780|title=Standings |date=2003|website=resources.motogp.com |format=PDF|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref>\n\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Riders' Championship standings\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! {{Tooltip|Pos.|Position}}\n! Rider\