rdon 124\">Mardon 124</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\"|<span style=\"font-size: 90%;\">'''Turnout '''</span>\n|-\n{{CANelec|AB|Liberal|Alexander C. Rutherford|1,034|85.9%}}\n{{Canadian_politics/party_colours/Progressive Conservatives/row}}\n|[[Alberta Progressive Conservative Party|Conservative]]\n|[[Rice Sheppard]]\n|align=\"right\"|173\n|align=\"right\"|14.1%\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" align=center|'''[[1905 Alberta general election]] results ([[Strathcona (provincial electoral district)|Strathcona]])'''<ref name=\"Mardon 124\"/>\n| colspan=\"2\"|<span style=\"font-size: 90%;\">'''Turnout '''</span>\n|-\n{{CANelec|AB|Liberal|Alexander C. Rutherford|625|67.1%}}\n{{Canadian_politics/party_colours/Progressive Conservatives/row}}\n|[[Alberta Progressive Conservative Party|Conservative]]\n|Frank W. Crang\n|align=\"right\"|306\n|align=\"right\"|32.9%\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" align=center|'''[[1902 Northwest Territories general election]] results ([[Strathcona (N.W.T. electoral district)|Strathcona]])'''<ref name=\"NWT elections\">{{cite web |url=http://www.saskarchives.com/web/seld/1-00.pdf |format=PDF|title=Territories |publisher=Saskatchewan Archives Board |accessdate=2008-01-23| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070928101028/http://www.saskarchives.com/web/seld/1-00.pdf| archivedate = September 28, 2007}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\"|<span style=\"font-size: 90%;\">'''Turnout '''</span>\n|-\n|colspan=\"2\"|\n|Alexander C. Rutherford\n|align=\"right\"|577\n|align=\"right\"|89.5%\n|-\n|colspan=\"2\"|\n|N.D. Mills\n|align=\"right\"|68\n|align=\"right\"|10.5%\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" align=center|'''[[1898 Northwest Territories general election]] results ([[Edmonton (N.W.T. electoral district)|Edmonton]])'''<ref name=\"NWT elections\"/>\n| colspan=\"2\"|<span style=\"font-size: 90%;\">'''Turnout '''</span>\n|-\n|colspan=\"2\"|\n|[[Matthew McCauley (politician)|Matthew McCauley]]\n|align=\"right\"|582\n|align=\"right\"|48.8%\n|-\n|colspan=\"2\"|\n|Alexander C. Rutherford\n|align=\"right\"|498